        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add /goal session continuation command",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add a bundled `goal` extension with `/goal help`, `/goal start`, `/goal status`, `/goal events`, `/goal pause`, `/goal resume`, `/goal done`, and `/goal clear`\n- add a `goal_status` tool so the active session can report `continue`, `done`, `blocked`, `paused`, or `waiting_approval`\n- store one visible goal state per trusted session\n- use the continuation lease API from the scaffold PR to enqueue one same-session follow-up turn\n- add stop gates, terminal states, and a continuation cap\n\n## Dependency\n\nDepends on the scaffold PR: #85722.\n\nThis PR is stacked on the scaffold branch locally so maintainers can review the runtime contract separately from the user-facing feature. On GitHub it targets `main`; until #85722 merges, the diff may include the scaffold changes as well. I am happy to keep the two PRs stacked, retarget after #85722 lands, or combine them if maintainers prefer one review thread.\n\n## Why\n\nThe scaffold PR is deliberately small, but a runtime primitive is hard to judge without a real user flow. `/goal` is that user flow: a human starts an objective, inspects what happened, pauses or resumes continuation, and finishes or clears the goal while the model can request only bounded same-session continuation through `goal_status`.\n\nThe user experience is not only \"let the agent continue.\" It is also \"let the human see whether the agent is behaving well enough to keep continuing.\" That matters across model tiers: a frontier model may stay on target most of the time, but cheaper or smaller models need tighter rails, clearer stop states, and a visible decision trail so users can trust, pause, resume, or stop work without guessing.\n\nThis is why the command surface includes both lifecycle controls and lightweight observability. `/goal status` shows the current state; `/goal events` shows the recent decision trail. The user does not need a dashboard or debug mode to answer the basic question: \"is this still doing the right thing?\"\n\n## Safety\n\n- slash-command session context is host-owned\n- `goal_status` uses trusted tool context, not model-supplied `sessionKey` or `goalId`\n- model-driven `continue` is accepted only while the current goal is already in `continue`\n- `done` and `blocked` are terminal for `/goal resume`; start a new goal to continue\n- `paused` stops continuation until a human resumes\n- `clear` removes the active user-facing goal state and clears any matching continuation lease\n- continuation count is capped; hitting the cap moves the goal to `waiting_approval`, clears the lease, and tells the user to start a new goal\n- no cross-session targeting, no fanout, no silent wake modes, no sub-agent continuation\n\n## Commands\n\n```text\n/goal help\n/goal start <objective>\n/goal status\n/goal events [n]\n/goal pause\n/goal resume\n/goal done [note]\n/goal clear [note]\n```\n\n## Tests\n\n```text\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/goal/index.test.ts\npnpm test:extensions:batch -- goal\npnpm tsgo:extensions:test\npnpm exec oxlint extensions/goal/index.ts extensions/goal/index.test.ts \\\n  extensions/goal/src/command.ts extensions/goal/src/state.ts \\\n  extensions/goal/src/tool.ts extensions/goal/src/workflow.ts\npnpm build\n```\n\nPlugin guardrails also passed on the stacked branch:\n\n```text\npnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.contracts-plugin.config.ts \\\n  src/plugins/contracts/package-manifest.contract.test.ts \\\n  src/plugins/contracts/plugin-entry-guardrails.test.ts \\\n  src/plugins/contracts/plugin-tool-contracts.test.ts\n```\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** A user can start a session goal, inspect status, inspect the recent event trail, pause continuation, clear the goal, and the command handler only uses the trusted session context.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw checkout `tmp/upstream-prs/openclaw-goal` on branch `goal-command-minimal`, commit `3abbf4a999`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran a live `pnpm exec tsx` command in the checkout that imports `handleGoalCommand` from `extensions/goal/src/command.ts`, uses a temporary in-memory store and fake workflow host API, then executes `/goal start`, `/goal status`, `/goal events`, `/goal pause`, `/goal events`, and `/goal clear` against trusted session key `agent:proof:session`.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from that command:\n\n```text\n$ /goal start prove goal continuation\nGoal started: prove goal continuation\nContinuation: scheduled\n$ /goal status\nGoal: prove goal continuation\nStatus: continue\nContinuations: 1\n$ /goal events 5\n2026-05-23T13:49:28.260Z created continue\n2026-05-23T13:49:28.260Z lease_scheduled continue\n$ /goal pause reviewer checkpoint\nGoal: prove goal continuation\nStatus: paused\nContinuations: 1\nNote: reviewer checkpoint\n$ /goal events 5\n2026-05-23T13:49:28.260Z created continue\n2026-05-23T13:49:28.260Z lease_scheduled continue\n2026-05-23T13:49:28.261Z status paused - reviewer checkpoint\n$ /goal clear finished proof\nGoal cleared: prove goal continuation\nworkflow calls [[\"request\",\"active-goal\",\"agent:proof:session\"],[\"clear\",\"active-goal\",\"agent:proof:session\"],[\"clear\",\"active-goal\",\"agent:proof:session\"]]\nremaining state 0\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** The command flow scheduled one same-session continuation lease, exposed current state via `/goal status`, exposed the decision trail via `/goal events`, cleared continuation on pause/clear, and removed visible goal state on clear (`remaining state 0`).\n- **What was not tested:** No real Discord/WhatsApp slash-command adapter was exercised locally; the proof runs the actual bundled extension command handler and workflow calls in-process.\n\n## Known local check noise\n\nAfter ClawSweeper review, the branch was amended to use a flat string enum schema for `goal_status.status` and to return the declared `scheduled` continuation-test-helper result shape.\n\nFull `pnpm check` reached the repo lint phase and failed on an unrelated pre-existing lint issue in `extensions/signal/src/daemon.ts` (`__testing` dangling underscore). The touched `/goal` and workflow files pass targeted lint, typecheck, plugin guardrails, and build.\n\n",
